    • Constructor Detail

      • ServiceSession

        public ServiceSession()
        This class represents PM API service requests and responses. Client code should use this object as a means of communicating with (writing/reading to/from) Predix Mobile services which have been registered with the ServiceRouter

      • ServiceSession

        public ServiceSession(URLRequest request,
                      PMAPIResponseHandler responseHandler)
        Constructs a ServiceSession with a request and a response handler. Data for a given service is read from the URLRequest while data returned by the service is given to the PMAPIResponseHandler
        Parameters:
        request - The URLRequest containing a PM API RESTful service call
        responseHandler - a PMAPIResponseHandler that is invoked when the invoked service is finished responding.

      • ServiceSession

        public ServiceSession(URLRequest request,
                      URLResponse response,
                      PMAPIResponseHandler responseHandler)
        Constructs a ServiceSession with a request and a response handler. Data for a given service is read from the URLRequest while data returned by the service is given to the PMAPIResponseHandler
        Parameters:
        request - The URLRequest containing a PM API RESTful service call
        response - The URLResponse where data returned from the service can be read.
        responseHandler - a PMAPIResponseHandler that is invoked when the invoked service is finished responding.

      • dataReturn

        public void dataReturn(byte[] data)
        Called incrementally by the service in the case of chunked or progressive HTTP behavior. If a service cannot return all the data at once it can optionally call this method to deliver data in pieces.
        Parameters:
        data - a byte array containing data to return to the client.

      • respondAndCompleteSession

        public void respondAndCompleteSession()
        Responds to the caller with the response object for the session and completes the session.

      • completeSession

        public void completeSession()
        Called by the service to complete the communication. This method is used in conjunction with dataReturn when data needs to be returned incrementally or in chunks. After the last chunk is sent a service should invoke this method to signal calling client that the request is complete.

      • respondWithStatusCodeAndBody

        public void respondWithStatusCodeAndBody(int status,
                                         java.lang.String bodyString)
        When a service wishes to respond to client in one call this method can be used. It sends raw text data with a response code back to the calling client.
        Parameters:
        status - Any HTTP status code.
        bodyString - The raw text response from the servie.

      • respondWithStatusCodeAndJSON

        public void respondWithStatusCodeAndJSON(int status,
                                         org.json.JSONObject json)
        When a service wishes to respond to client in one call this method can be used. It sends a JSON response back to the calling client.
        Parameters:
        status - Any HTTP status code.
        json - A JSONObject containing the service response.

      • respondWithStatusCode

        @Deprecated
public void respondWithStatusCode(int status)
        Deprecated. use respondWithStatusCodeAndCompleteSession
        When a service needs to send a response code only then this method should be called. It can be used in scenarios where the full response may take time to complete. An example would be a service which opens a dialog to collect information from the user. In such case the service could respond initially with an HTTP 200 status code and send the remaining response date in a later method call.
        Parameters:
        status - an HTTP status code.
